    {
      "source": "target",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The straight-line depreciation formula is (Cost - Salvage Value) / Useful Life. Plugging in your numbers, the annual depreciation is (50,000 - 5,000) / 5, which equals 9,000 per year. This means your heavy machinery loses 9,000 in value each year until it reaches its salvage value. You can subtract this 9,000 from the book value every year to track the asset's depreciation over its five-year lifespan.",
